## 🏗️ Project 2: Infrastructure Layout — Raised Floor & Cable Management
**Objective:** Structural design for airflow efficiency and multi-tier cable segregation.

### 1. Raised Floor & Airflow Architecture
* **System:** Bolted stringer understructure with $600\text{mm} \times 600\text{mm}$ HPL antistatic tiles.
* **Plenum Height:** **450mm Finished Floor Height (FFH)** to facilitate optimal static pressure for underfloor cooling.
* **Containment:** **Hot Aisle Containment (HAC)** specified to prevent air bypass and improve PUE (Power Usage Effectiveness).

### 2. Multi-Tier Cable Segregation Strategy
To mitigate EMI and maximize "Day 2" maintenance efficiency, the following hierarchy was designed:

| Tier | Layer | Media Type | Technical Logic |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Tier A** | Underfloor | Power (A+B Feeds) | Keeps heavy cabling out of signal path; optimizes plenum space. |
| **Tier B** | Overhead | Data / Fiber Optic | Allows rapid patching changes without disrupting airflow. |

